Vite copies everything in public/ into dist/ on build, including this file.

That is deliberate. web/dist/.gitkeep is tracked in git so `go build` succeeds
via go:embed in a fresh checkout that has never run `npm run build` — go:embed
fails outright if the embedded directory does not exist. Because Vite empties
dist/ on every build, without this copy the tracked placeholder would be
deleted by each build and show up as a spurious git deletion.

This file is never served in any meaningful sense; it just guarantees dist/ is
non-empty.
